 indicator.</p>\r\n', '<p>Legislation/policies developed/updated with the support of the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('577', '45', '8468', 'Number of police officers trained by the Action on DDR challenges and the available support services (disaggregated by sex)', 'Number of', '<p>The more specific you can be about the training topics and target participants in the local context - the better.</p>\r\n', '<p>Database of training participants, disaggregated by sex&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('578', '45', '8468', 'Number of national or local strategies on DDR designed with the support of the Action', 'Number of', '<p>If only one strategy is foreseen, please change the formulation of the indicator to &quot;Status of&quot;.</p>\r\n', '<p>Strategy document</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('579', '45', '8468', 'Number of ex-combattants benefitting from psycho-social support / VET training (or similar services) provided by the Action (disaggregated by sex and age)', 'Number of', '<p>The more specific you can be about the type of support to be provided in the local context - the better.</p>\r\n', '<p>Database of training participants, disaggregated by sex&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('580', '45', '8468', 'Number of persons reached by public awareness campaigns on the importance of DDR and promoting the re-integration of ex-combattants (or related topics) implemented with the support of the Action', 'Number of', '<p>This number can be obtained either by collecting information about people who participate in events organized by the project, or based on the data from the listenership surveys (if the project supports the development of a radio/TV programme, for example)</p>\r\n', '<p>Project&#39;s database of event participants, listenership surveys of radio/TV programmes developed by the project</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('582', '42', '8373', 'Proportion of the target population (resident/host communities and displaced persons) living below the national poverty lin