population (resident/host communities and displaced persons) who report that they feel safe walking outside alone in the evening (disaggregated by sex)', 'Percentage', '<p>Percentage of the target population (resident/host communities and displaced persons) who report that they feel safe walking outside alone in the evening (disaggregated by sex)</p>\r\n', '<p>Survey of the target population to be implemented by the Action at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('613', '42', '8371', 'Percentage of children in target population (resident/host communities and displaced persons) aged 12-23 months immunized against measles  (disaggregated by displacement status)', 'Percentage', '<p>Please check if data disaggregation for displaced persons is available for your country/ies. If data is not available, please foresee baseline and final studies to be commissioned by the Action.</p>\r\n', '<p>For the population in general: World Bank, <a href=\"http://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx?source=world-development-indicators\">http://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx?source=world-development-indicators</a>.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('611', '42', '8371', 'Percentage of the target population (resident/host communities and displaced persons) with access to an improved water source (disaggregated by displacement status)', 'Percentage', '<p>Target population should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>For the population in general: World Bank, <a href=\"http://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx?source=world-development-indicators\">http://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx?source=world-development-indicators</a>. The project may need to commission baseline and final studies to obtain data for the displaced population.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('612', '42', '8371', 'Number of incidences of physical, psychological or sexual violence reported by the target population (resident/host communities and displaced persons) to competent authorities (disaggregated by displacement status)', 'Number of', '<p>Target population should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Police records or baseline and final surveys of displaced and host communities if the Action has sufficient funding.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary (primary if the project commissions surveys)', '0'), ('610', '42', '8371', 'Percentage of the target population (resident/host communities and displaced persons) with access to improved sanitation facilities (disaggregated by displacement status)', 'Percentage', '<p>Target population should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>For the population in general: World Bank, <a href=\"http://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx?source=world-development-indicators\">http://databank.worldbank.org/data/reports.aspx?source=world-development-indicators</a>. The project may need to commission baseline and final studies to obtain data for the displaced population.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('609', '42', '8369', 'Percentage of displaced persons whose solution is in line with their expressed preference (integration in host community/country or return)', 'Percentage', '', '<p>Survey of displaced persons/returnees to be implemented by the Action at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('608', '42', '8369', 'Number of persons who return (disaggregated by sex)', 'Number of', '<p>This indicator measures the number of persons who return to their community/country of origin where they were forcibly displaced from.</p>\r\n', '<p>Government statistics to the extent they are available. The project may also need to commission baseline and final studies.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('605', '42', '8369', 'Number of displaced persons who acquire permanent residence or nationality / elect residence in their area', 'Number of', '', '<p>Ministry of Interior report to be requested by the Action</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('606', '42', '8369', 'Number of displaced persons acquiring long-term residence in a third country (resettlement, familiy reunification) / elect residence in a third area', 'Number of', '', '<p>Ministry of Interior report to be requested by the Action</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('607', '42', '8369', 'Number of displaced persons acquiring medium-term residence in a third country (study, work opportunity, temporary protection arrangement)', 'Number of', '', '<p>Ministry of Interior report to be requested by the Action</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('598', '42', '8368', 'Percentage of host/resident community members who would welcome a forcibly displaced person in their family as a son/daughter in law', 'Percentage', '<p>If the project aims to shift public attitudes towards forcibly displaced persons, direct and proxy questions could be combined in a survey of host/resident communities. The survey should be conducted at least twice, at the beginning and at the end of the Action, to enable the evaluation of results.</p>\r\n', '<p>Public perceptions survey of resident/host communities to be implemented by the Action at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('599', '42', '8368', 'Percentage of host/resident community members who would welcome forcibly displaced persons to stay in their city/village permanently', 'Percentage', '<p>If the project aims to shift public attitudes towards forcibly displaced persons, direct and proxy questions could be combined in a survey of host/resident communities. The survey should be conducted at least twice, at the beginning and at the end of the Action, to enable the evaluation of results.</p>\r\n', '<p>Public perceptions survey of resident/host communities to be implemented by the Action at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('600', '42', '8368', 'Extent to which national policies reflect recommendations provided by displaced persons and their organizations', 'Scale', '<p>Ideally, you will be able to select some specific policies to be followed and examined. A scale for describing the extent to which these policies reflect recommendations provided by displaced persons and their organizations can include: 1 - to a significant extent (there was substantive engagement with displaced persons and all recommendations provided were adopted in the final formulation of the policy), 2 - to some extent (there were several consultation meetings and the government engaged in discussion with displaced persons, with some recommendations being adopted), 3 - to a limited extent (there was at least one consultation meeting and a couple of the proposals were adopted, but for the most part the recommendations provided by displaced persons were not addressed, 4 - to no extent (there was no consultation meeting or discussion engaging both the government and displaced persons and none of the displaced persons&#39; recommendations were adopted).</p>\r\n', '<p>Qualitative analysis of the final policy (including interviews with the government and displaced persons who provided inputs), commissioned by the project.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('601', '42', '8368', 'Proportion of displaced persons subjected to physical, psychological or sexual violence since becoming displaced or in the last 6 months (whichever is more recent)', 'Percentage', '<p>Adapted from SDG indicator 16.1.3.</p>\r\n', '<p>Survey of displaced persons to be implemented by the Action at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('602', '42', '8368', 'Number of conflicts between and among displaced and host communities', 'Number of', '', '<p>Police records or baseline and final surveys of displaced and host communities if the Action has sufficient funding.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary (primary if the project commissions surveys)', '0'), ('603', '42', '8368', 'Number of displaced persons reporting having personally felt discriminated against or harassed in the previous 12 months on the basis of a ground of discrimination prohibited under international human rights law ', 'Number of', '<p>SDG indicators 10.3.1 &amp; 16.b.1</p>\r\n', '<p>Survey of displaced persons to be implemented by the Action at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('604', '42', '8368', 'Percentage of host/resident community members who would welcome a forcibly displaced person as a neighbour', 'Percentage', '<p>If the project aims to shift public attitudes towards forcibly displaced persons, direct and proxy questions could be combined in a survey of host/resident communities. The survey should be conducted at least twice, at the beginning and at the end of the Action, to enable the evaluation of results.</p>\r\n', '<p>Public perceptions survey of resident/host communities to be implemented by the Action at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('615', '42', '8371', 'Participation rate of youth and adults in formal and non-formal education and training in the previous 12 months (disaggregated by sex and displacement status)', 'Percentage', '<p>SDG indicator 4.3.1</p>\r\n', '<p>UN SDG reports in the first and last year of the Action. The project may also need to commission baseline and final studies to obtain data.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('616', '42', '8371', 'Prevalence of moderate or severe food insecurity in the past year (%)', 'Percentage', '<p>Food Insecurity Experience Scale (FIES) SDG indicator 2.1.2</p>\r\n', '<p>UN SDG reports in the first and last year of the Action. The project may also need to commission baseline and final studies to obtain data.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary (primary if the project commissions surveys)', '0'), ('617', '42', '8371', 'Percentage of displaced persons having their asylum claim assessed in a procedure in line with international standards', 'Percentage', '', '<p>UN SDG reports in the first and last year of the Action. The project may also need to commission baseline and final studies to obtain data.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary (primary if the project commissions surveys)', '0'), ('618', '42', '8371', 'Percentage of the target population where at least one person in household has a bank account ', 'Percentage', '<p>Target population should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Survey of the target population to be implemented by the Action at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('619', '42', '8371', 'Proportion of the target population (resident/host communities and displaced persons) in urban areas living in slums, informal settlements or inadequate housing  (disaggregated by displacement status)', 'Percentage', '<p>Adapted from SDG indicator 11.1.1.</p>\r\n', '<p>UN SDG reports in the first and last year of the Action. The project may also need to commission baseline and final studies to obtain data.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary (primary if the project commissions surveys)', '0'), ('620', '42', '8371', 'Percentage of the target population (resident/host communities and displaced persons) without civil registration documents (disaggregated by sex, age and displacement status)', 'Percentage', '<p>ID documents can include registration of displacement, birth certificate, identity card - please specify in the indicator which type of document when you are interested in.</p>\r\n', '<p>UN statistics if available for the given population. Otherwise the project needs to commission a survey of the target population at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary (primary if the project commissions surveys)', '0'), ('621', '42', '8372', 'Average income of the target population (resident/host communities, including displaced persons), disaggregated by displacement status', 'Currency (EUR or local currency)', '<p>Target population should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Survey of target beneficiaries to be implemented by the Action at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('622', '42', '8372', 'Number of target beneficiaries (resident/host communities and displaced persons) accessing social insurance schemes  (disaggregated by displacement status)', 'Number of', '<p>Beneficiaries should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Report from the relevant line ministry. If data is not available, the project will need to commission a survey of target beneficiaries.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary (primary if the project commissions surveys)', '0'), ('623', '42', '8372', 'Number of target beneficiaries (resident/host communities and displaced persons) accessing healthcare under the national insurance scheme  (disaggregated by displacement status)', 'Number of', '<p>Beneficiaries should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Report from the relevant line ministry. If data is not available, the project will need to commission a survey of target beneficiaries.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary (primary if the project commissions surveys)', '0'), ('624', '42', '8372', 'Number of target beneficiaries (resident/host communities and displaced persons) receiving basic income security payments from a national scheme if unable to earn an income  (disaggregated by displacement status)', 'Number of', '<p>Beneficiaries should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Report from the relevant line ministry. If data is not available, the project will need to commission a survey of target beneficiaries.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary (primary if the project commissions surveys)', '0'), ('625', '42', '8372', 'Number of target beneficiaries (resident/host communities and displaced persons) who engage in negative coping mechanisms such as early marriage (under the legal age), child labour and prostitution (disaggregated by displacement status)', 'Number of', '<p>Beneficiaries should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Survey of target beneficiaries to be implemented by the Action at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('626', '42', '8372', 'Number of target beneficiaries (resident/host communities and displaced persons) facing restrictions to their freedom of movement (disaggregated by sex and displacement status)', 'Number of', '<p>Beneficiaries should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Survey of target beneficiaries to be implemented by the Action at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('627', '42', '8372', 'Agricultural target population with ownership or secure rights or use rights over agricultural land', 'Number of', '<p>Beneficiaries should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Survey of target beneficiaries to be implemented by the Action at the beginning and end of implementation.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('628', '42', '8372', 'Number (and %) of target beneficiaries (resident/host communities and displaced persons) gainfully (self)employed (disaggregated by displacement status)', 'Number of (and percentage of)', '<p>Beneficiaries should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Report from the relevant line ministry. If data is not available, the project will need to commission a survey of target beneficiaries.</p>\r\n', 'Secondary (primary if the project commissions surveys)', '0'), ('629', '42', '8356', 'Number of persons participating in local projects aiming to combat discrimination against displaced persons (disaggregated by sex, displacement status)', 'Number of', '<p>This can include conference participants, participants who joined a community activity supported by the Action, etc.</p>\r\n', '<p>Progress reports for the Action - please ensure the implementing partners record participants for each event disaggregated by sex, displacement status</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('630', '42', '8356', 'Number of people reached through advocacy/media programmes aiming to combat discrimination against displaced persons ', 'Number of ', '<p>This can include, for example, the estimated listenership of radio/TV shows commissioned/broadcast with Action support, or the number of people who visited a website developed by the Action</p>\r\n', '<p>Progress reports for the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('631', '42', '8358', 'Number of laws, policies and strategies addressing displacement and return-related challenges and opportunities revised/drafted with Action support', 'Number of', '<p>If the Action aims to support the revision/drafting of a specific policy, please reformulate this indicator to: Status of [state title of policy/law]</p>\r\n', '<p>Text of the relevant law/policy, progress reports for the Action describing its contribution</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('632', '42', '8360', 'Number of roundtables/workshops/conferences organized by the Action to promote debate on a draft policy/law addressing displacement or return issues', 'Number of', '', '<p>Event report, submitted as part of the Action progress report</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('633', '42', '8360', 'Number of participants at roundtables/workshops/conferences organized by the Action to promote debate on a draft policy/law addressing displacement or return issues (disagregated by sex, displacement status)', 'Number of', '', '<p>Database of event participants and statistics provided in the Action progress reports (disagregated by sex, displacement status)</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('634', '42', '8361', 'Number of civil society projects promoting social cohesion and conflict prevention between host/resident communities and displaced persons/returnees supported by the Action', 'Number of ', '<p>Please specify in the indicator whether your Action will target host or resident communities - and displaced persons or returnees.</p>\r\n', '<p>Progress reports for the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('635', '42', '8361', 'Number of persons involved in local reconciliation initiatives, confidence-building initiatives, or formal peace processes (e.g. local peace committees, public debates, forums, cross-community activities and others) in last 12 months (disaggregated b', 'Number of', '<p>This can include conference participants, participants who joined a community activity supported by the Action, etc.</p>\r\n', '<p>Progress reports for the Action - please ensure the implementing partners record participants for each event disaggregated by sex and displacement status</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('636', '42', '8361', 'Number of community mediators trained on conflict prevention and peaceful conflict mediation (disaggregated by sex, location, displacement status)', 'Number of', '', '<p>Database of training participants and statistics to be provided in progress reports for the Action (disaggregated by sex, location, displacement status)</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('637', '42', '8361', 'Number of people reached through media programmes aiming to promote social cohesion and conflict prevention between host/resident communities and displaced persons/returnees ', 'Number of ', '<p>This can include, for example, the estimated listenership of radio/TV shows commissioned/broadcast with Action support, or the number of people who visited a website developed by the Action. Please specify in the indicator whether your Action will target host or resident communities - and displaced persons or returnees.</p>\r\n', '<p>Progress reports for the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('638', '42', '8479', 'Status of availability of quantitative and qualitative data provide d by this action on the impact of the displacement situation, e.g. with regard to perspectives for solutions, protection, basic services, housing, employment, and environment', 'Status of ', '', '<p>Capacity assessment study to be commissioned by the Action</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('639', '42', '8362', 'Number of civil society projects on eliminating barriers to access to services for displaced persons supported by the Action', 'Number of ', '', '<p>Progress reports for the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('640', '42', '8362', 'Number of persons engaged in local projects aiming to eliminate barriers to access to services for displaced persons (disaggregated by sex, displacement status)', 'Number of', '<p>This can include conference participants, participants who joined a community activity supported by the Action, etc.</p>\r\n', '<p>Progress reports for the Action - please ensure the implementing partners record participants for each event disaggregated by sex, displacement status</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('641', '42', '8362', 'Number of people reached through media programmes aiming to eliminate barriers to access to services for displaced persons ', 'Number of ', '<p>This can include, for example, the estimated listenership of radio/TV shows commissioned/broadcast with Action support, or the number of people who visited a website developed by the Action</p>\r\n', '<p>Progress reports for the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('642', '42', '8364', 'Number of service providers trained/recruited (i.e. for Budget Support Actions) by the Action for coverage of additional population (disaggregated by sex, location and service sector)', 'Number of', '<p>Please specify the relevant service sectors and training topics</p>\r\n', '<p>Database of training participants/new staff recruited (disaggregated by sex, location, sector) and statistics to be provided in progress reports for the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('643', '42', '8364', 'Number of persons benefitting from improved infrastructure, or human/technical/financial resources provided with support from the action (disaggregated by sex and displacement status)', 'Number of', '<p>Beneficiaries should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Progress reports for the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('644', '42', '8364', 'Number of infrastructure/facilities rehabilitated, enhanced or constructed with support of the action', 'Number of', '', '<p>Progress reports for the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('645', '42', '8365', 'Number of service providers trained for responding to the specific needs and vulnerabilities of displaced persons (disaggregated by sex, location and service sector)', 'Number of', '<p>Please specify the relevant service sectors and training topics</p>\r\n', '<p>Database of training participants (disaggregated by sex, location, sector) and statistics to be provided in progress reports for the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('646', '42', '8363', 'Number of beneficiaries who received legal or practical aid through this action to resolve competing claims to housing, land and assets (disaggregated by type of claim, sex, location, age and displacement status)', 'Number of', '<p>Beneficiaries should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Database of beneficiaries (disaggregated by sex, location, type of document, age and displacement status) and statistics to be provided in progress reports for the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('647', '42', '8366', 'Number of beneficiaries receiving vocational education and training (VET) or entrepreneurial training through this Action (disaggregated by sex, location, training topic and duration, age and displacement status)', 'Number of', '<p>Beneficiaries should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Database of training participants (disaggregated by sex, location, training topic and duration, age and displacement status) and statistics to be provided in progress reports for the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('648', '42', '8367', 'Number of beneficiaries who obtained civil registration documents with support of the action (disaggregated by sex, age and type of document)', 'Number of', '<p>ID documents can include registration of displacement, birth certificate, identity card - please specify in the indicator which type of document when you are interested in. Beneficiaries should include not only displaced persons but also members of resident/host communities.</p>\r\n', '<p>Database of beneficiaries (disaggregated by sex, location, type of document, age and displacement status) and statistics to be provided in progress reports for the Action</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('786', '45', '8451', 'Number of confirmed cases where civilian control was not properly exercised', 'Number of', '', '<p>Oversight bodies&#39; reports, civil society reports</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('650', '45', '8455', 'Proportion of population that feel safe walking alone around the area they live ', 'Percentage', '', '<p>UNODC reports</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('651', '45', '8456', 'Number of ex-combattants that were effectively integrated into their communities after giving up arms', 'Number of', '<p>Please add detail to this indicator to define what &quot;effectively integrated&quot; means in the local context, i.e. finding employment, finding a fixed residence.</p>\r\n', '<p>This indicator will likely require primary data collection through a survey or similar study, implemented by the Action.</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('652', '45', '8465', 'Number of detention facilities that comply international standards thanks to support of this Action', 'Number of', '', '<p>Progress reports</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('653', '45', '8465', 'Number of [types of equipment - please specify] that are put in service with the support of this Action', 'Number of', '<p>Please specify the type of equipment the Action will provide.</p>\r\n', '<p>Progress reports</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('654', '48', '8597', 'Employment-to-population ratio, by sex and other relevant groups', 'Percentage', '<p>The employment-to-population ratio is the proportion of a country&rsquo;s working- age population that is employed.<br />\r\nOther relevant groups may include ethnicity, migration status, disability, etc, where specific data might needs to be collected from national surveys.<br />\r\nEmployment comprises all persons of working age who during a specified brief period, such as one week or one day, were in the following categories: a) paid employment; or b) self-employment<br />\r\nThis could be ILO modelled data or national estimates</p>\r\n', '<p>ILO<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWorld Bank<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'secondary data', '0'), ('655', '48', '8597', 'Proportion of informal employment in non-agriculture employment, by sex', 'Percentage', '<p>SDG indicator but currently a tier 2 indicator (Indicator conceptually clear, established methodology and standards available but data not regularly produced by countries). So check availability for your country of interest before using<br />\r\nCustodian agencies: ILO</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"https://unstats.un.org/sdgs/indicators/database/?indicator=8.3.1\">SDG indicators database</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'secondary indicator', '0'), ('656', '48', '8597', 'Employment rate, disaggregated by sex and other relevant groups', 'Percentage', '<p>The employment rate is the percentage of people in the labour force that are employed.<br />\r\nOther relevant groups maybe include ethnicity, migration status, disability, etc, where specific data might needs be to&nbsp;collected from national surveys,<br />\r\nFollowing the ILO definitions:<br />\r\nThe labour force is the sum of the number of persons employed and the number of persons unemployed.<br />\r\nEmployment comprises all persons of working age who during a specified brief period, such as one week or one day, were in the following categories: a) paid employment ; or b) self-employment.<br />\r\nThe unemployed comprise all persons of working age who were: a) without work during the reference period; b) currently available for work; and c) seeking work</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"http://www.ilo.org/ilostat/faces/wcnav_defaultSelection?_afrLoop=778708074945114&amp;_afrWindowMode=0&amp;_afrWindowId=null#!%40%40%3F_afrWindowId%3Dnull%26_afrLoop%3D778708074945114%26_afrWindowMode%3D0%26_adf.ctrl-state%3Dju9g8dq6b_120\">ILO</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0');
INSERT INTO `legacy_web_indicators` VALUES ('657', '48', '8597', 'Proportion of employed people living below the international poverty link, by sex and other relevant groups', 'Percentage', '<p><a href=\"https://europa.eu/capacity4dev/eu-rfi\">The working poor are defined as employed persons living in households in which per capita consumption is below the internationally defined poverty line of $1.90 (PPP) per day<br />\r\nPlease refer to the method note for the EU RF indicator for further information on calculations.</a></p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"https://unstats.un.org/sdgs/indicators/database/?indicator=1.1.1\">SDG indicators database</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'secondary data', '0'), ('658', '48', '8597', 'Real GDP growth, (i) latest year and (ii) average over last 5 years', 'Percentage', '<p><a href=\"https://europa.eu/capacity4dev/eu-rfi\">Please refer to the method note for the EU RF indicator for further information on calculations.</a></p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"http://www.imf.org/external/ns/cs.aspx?id=28\">IMF World Economic Outlook database</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'secondary data', '0'), ('659', '48', '8597', 'Annual growth rate of real GDP per employed person', 'Percentage', '<p>SDG Tier I indicator<br />\r\nCustodian agencies: ILO, World Bank, UNSD</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"https://unstats.un.org/sdgs/indicators/database/?indicator=8.2.1\">SDG indicator database</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('660', '48', '8597', 'Annual growth rate of real GDP per capita', 'Percentage', '<p>Tier I indicator<br />\r\nCustodian agencies: World Bank, UNSD</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/NY.GDP.PCAP.KD.ZG\">World Bank</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('661', '48', '8597', '[placeholder – ESFD employment/job related indicator]', 'tbc', '<p>the External Investment Plan&nbsp;may have a specific employment/job related indicator. If and when this is finalised, this will be included accordingly.</p>\r\n', '<p>tbc</p>\r\n', 'tbc', '0'), ('662', '48', '8598', 'Global Competitiveness Index', 'Ranking', '<p><a href=\"https://europa.eu/capacity4dev/eu-rfi\">The Global Competitiveness Report 2014-2015 assesses the competitiveness landscape of 144 economies, providing insight into the drivers of their productivity and prosperity.<br />\r\nPlease refer to the method note for the EU RF indicator for further information on calculations.</a></p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"http://reports.weforum.org/global-competitiveness-report-2014-2015/\">World Economic Forum</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('663', '48', '8598', 'Value added of manufacturing as % of GDP', 'Percentage', '<p>This gives some indications on whether the economy is moving towards higher-value sectors, e.g. manufacturing. Other higher value sectors may be chosen for the indicator. However, the data availability/quality/reliability may be an issue.</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/NV.IND.MANF.ZS\">World Bank,<br />\r\n<br />\r\nnational accounts</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('664', '48', '8598', 'Value added of sector/value chain [X] (% GDP)', 'Percentage', '<p>If information on a specific value chain is needed, it&#39;s very likely specific surveys/studies will be needed as part of the intervention M&amp;E. Given the complexity and costs, please consider whether this option is viable before using this indicator.</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"https://data.worldbank.org/topic/economy-and-growth?view=chart\">Sector level: World Bank&nbsp;, national statistics<br />\r\n<br />\r\nValue chain: very likely intervention M&amp;E, surveys at least twice within the lifetime of the intervention.</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data, and/or primary data and expert analysis', '0'), ('665', '48', '8598', 'Value chain X value added per worker of sector/value [X]', 'Currency (EUR/$/local currency)', '<p>If information on a specific value chain is needed, it&#39;s very likely specific surveys/studies will be needed as part of the intervention M&amp;E. Given the complexity and costs, please consider whether this option is viable (e.g. costs/capability, etc) before using this indicator.</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"https://data.worldbank.org/topic/economy-and-growth?view=chart\">Sector level: World Bank&nbsp;, national statistics<br />\r\n<br />\r\nValue chain: very likely intervention M&amp;E, surveys at least twice within the lifetime of the intervention.</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data, and/or primary data and expert analysis', '0'), ('666', '48', '8599', 'Gross fixed capital formation (% of GDP)', 'Percentage', '', '<p><a href=\"http://data.worldbank.org/indicator/NE.GDI.FTOT.ZS\">World Bank</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('667', '48', '8599', 'Foreign direct investment net inflows as percent of GDP', 'Percentage', '<p>Estimates might vary between different sources due methodological differences, so please use one source (and hence estimation methodology) for programme monitoring.</p>\r\n', '<p>World Bank<br />\r\n<br />\r\nUNCTAD<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('668', '48', '8599', 'Domestic credit to private sector (% of GPD)', 'Percentage', '', '<p><a href=\"https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/FS.AST.PRVT.GD.ZS\">World Bank<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('669', '48', '8600', 'Export concentration index', 'Score', '<p>Concentration index, also named Herfindahl-Hirschmann Index (Product HHI), is a measure of the degree of product concentration.<br />\r\nThe index is valued between 0 and 1, where closer to 1 indicates a country&#39;s exports or imports are highly concentrated on a few products.</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"http://unctadstat.unctad.org/wds/ReportFolders/reportFolders.aspx?sCS_referer=&amp;sCS_ChosenLang=en\">UNCTAD</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('670', '48', '8600', 'Value of exports/ Export as % of GDP', 'Currency or Percentage', '', '<p><a href=\"https://data.worldbank.org/topic/economy-and-growth?view=chart\">World Bank</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('671', '48', '8600', 'Volume and value of intra-regional trade in [X] in supported region', 'Tonnes/MWh/etc**, Currency', '<p>[X] &ndash; please specify for your intervention. Could be goods, services, electricity, etc.<br />\r\n** exact unit will depend on the commodities/services chosen</p>\r\n', '<p>WTO and regional trade organisations<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('672', '48', '8601', 'Levels of private co-financing', 'Currency (€, $ , local currency)', '<p>Do not include financing from bilateral, multilateral or DFIs.<br />\r\nAt HQ, may need to disaggregate by EIP vs other programmes and projects.</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary source', '0'), ('673', '48', '8601', 'Number and value of Private Partnership in Infrastructure', 'Number and Currency', '<p>The Private Participation in Infrastructure (PPI) Project Database has data on over 6,400 infrastructure projects in 139 low- and middle-income countries. The database is the leading source of PPI trends in the developing world, covering projects in the energy, telecommunications, transport, and water and sewerage sectors. Projects include management or lease contracts, concessions, greenfield projects, and divestitures.</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"http://ppi.worldbank.org/\">World bank</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('674', '48', '8601', 'Number of new private sector firms investing in sector/value chain [X]', 'Number of firms', '<p>sector/value chain [X] &ndash; to be defined, which is most relevant to programme.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nCompare pre and post programme numbers to get the number of new firms</p>\r\n', '<p>Expert analysis of sector and/or value chain<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary + expert analysis', '0'), ('675', '48', '8601', 'Net taxes and fees paid to government by supported businesses or intermediaries', 'Currency', '<p>Periodic surveys (at least annual) as part of intervention M&amp;E</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('676', '48', '8602', 'World Bank\'s Overall Ease of Doing Business ranking and/or distance to the frontier score ', 'Number', '<p><a href=\"http://www.doingbusiness.org/data/distance-to-frontier\">This would normally be a national level or a high level outcome indicators or even may also be used at impact level for some programmes.<br />\r\nWorld Bank&#39;s Ease of Doing Business&nbsp;Ranking from 1 to 190, with 1 being the top ranking.<br />\r\nEase of Doing Business Distance to Frontier Score, from 0 to 100&nbsp; (higher the score means closer to the frontier)&nbsp;<br />\r\nImprovement of the business environment, measured as the &quot;Distance to frontier indicators&quot;:<br />\r\n-The distance to frontier score benchmarks economies with respect to regulatory best practice<br />\r\n-The ranking compares economies with one another based on the aggregate score. So the rank could decrease even if the frontier score has increased.<br />\r\nIt&#39;s more meaningful to monitor the score of the topic and/or at sub-national level that is most relevant to the project rather than looking at overall country score.<br />\r\nPlease note that some elements of the Doing Business surveys are largely based on measurements of the regulations rather than firm experience on the ground. So if possible programmes should also monitor the realities on the ground through additional enterprise surveys etc.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"http://www.doingbusiness.org/data\">World Bank&#39;s Doing Business report</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('677', '48', '8602', 'Burden of government regulation perceptions index', 'Score', '<p>Measures business executives&#39; perceptions of their country&#39;s government regulation burden: question asked is &quot;In your country, how burdensome is it for businesses to comply with governmental administrative requirements (e.g., permits, regulations, reporting)? [1 = extremely burdensome; 7 = not burdensome at all] &quot;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nNote this is only perceptions, and less likely to capture views of smallholder or micro business&#39;s opinions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"https://tcdata360.worldbank.org/indicators/govt.regu?country=BEL&amp;indicator=689&amp;viz=line_chart&amp;years=2007,2016\">WFE Global competitiveness index &ndash; sub indicator</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('678', '48', '8602', 'Actual number of days to comply with business regulations [or regulation X], disaggregated by type of firm, sex of head of firm', 'Number', '<p>Focus on actual times need to comply with regulations rather than the published times from official documentation and/or procedures.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nBusiness regulation can refer to all business regulations or specific reforms that the intervention has supported, e.g. days to obtain an operating license/construction related permit, etc. If the latter, then you need to specific in the indicator, e.g. actual number of days to comply with tax regulation, etc.</p>\r\n', '<p>Enterprise surveys as part of the intervention M&amp;E (at least twice within the lifetime of the programme)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data + expert analysis', '0'), ('679', '48', '8602', 'Percentage of business owners and managers who perceptive government regulation as very or fairly transparent disaggregated by sex of business owner/manager', 'Percentage', '<p>Please adapt the indicator according to the question you have</p>\r\n', '<p>Enterprise perception survey: pre- and post-reforms as part of intervention M&amp;E<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('680', '48', '8602', 'Percentage of enterprise owners and managers who rate the advice and services provided by the tax office as excellent or very good, disaggregated by enterprise size, sector and sex of enterprise owner/manager', 'Percentage', '<p>Please adapt the indicator according to the question you have</p>\r\n', '<p>Survey of enterprise owners/managers&nbsp;- before and after programme<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('681', '48', '8602', 'Land transfer cost as a percentage of property value ? taken from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018)', 'Percentage', '', '<p>At least two surveys of experts as part of intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary + expert analysis', '0'), ('682', '48', '8603', 'Number of newly registered firms disaggregated by sex of firm owner/head if relevant', 'Number', '<p>DCED Guidance: Data should be collected from the relevant government agencies. Newly registered firms: a firm registered with the business registry for the first time within the reporting period<br />\r\nPlease consider that the availability and accuracy of data depends on national statistics. For a certain time period the data related to close-down of business may be not up to date.<br />\r\nIf available, then useful to also measure business attrition rates within X years</p>\r\n', '<p>National statistics<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('683', '48', '8603', 'Number of private firms registered with the tax authority', 'Number of firms', '', '<p>depending on the nature of the intervention either intervention or official documents, at least twice as part of intervention M&amp;E</p>\r\n', 'Primary or secondary data', '0'), ('684', '48', '8603', 'Average number of year that firms operated without formal registration', 'Number', '<p>If planning to use the World Bank Enterprise Survey information, please check the availability and frequency of the surveys to assess suitable for monitoring purpose. If planning your own enterprise survey as part of the intervention, given the complexity and costs of such surveys, please consider whether this option is viable (e.g. costs/capacity, etc)&nbsp; before using this indicator.</p>\r\n', '<p>Enterprise surveys either carried out by the intervention or from alternative sources, e.g. the World Bank Enterprise surveys or national statistics office. At least two estimates are needed one for the baseline and one at the end of the intervention</p>\r\n', 'Primary or secondary data', '0'), ('685', '48', '8603', 'Percent of firms formally registered when started operations in the country', 'Percentage', '<p>If planning to use the World Bank Enterprise Survey information, please check the availability and frequency of the surveys to assess suitable for monitoring purpose. If planning your own enterprise survey as part of the intervention, given the complexity and costs of such surveys, please consider whether this option is viable (e.g. costs/capacity, etc)&nbsp; before using this indicator.</p>\r\n', '<p>Enterprise surveys either carried out by the intervention or from alternative sources, e.g. the World Bank Enterprise surveys or national statistics office. At least two estimates are needed one for the baseline and one at the end of the intervention</p>\r\n', 'Primary or secondary data', '0'), ('686', '48', '8603', 'Percent of firms competing against unregistered or informal firms', 'Percentage', '<p>If planning to use the World Bank Enterprise Survey information, please check the availability and frequency of the surveys to assess suitable for monitoring purpose. If planning your own enterprise survey as part of the intervention, given the complexity and costs of such surveys, please consider whether this option is viable (e.g. costs/capacity, etc)&nbsp; before using this indicator.</p>\r\n', '<p>Enterprise surveys either carried out by the intervention or from alternative sources, e.g. the World Bank Enterprise surveys or national statistics office. At least two estimates are needed one for the baseline and one at the end of the intervention</p>\r\n', 'Primary or secondary data', '0'), ('687', '48', '8604', 'Number of new (formal or informal) MSMEs linked to new value chains (national or international), disaggregated by sector and sex of MSME owner/head', 'Number M&SMEs', '<p>This will require in depth analyses by the programme to understand value chains at local level</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system and expert analysis<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('688', '48', '8604', '‘’DB Trading across borders’’ ranking and score', 'Ranking and score (percentage points)', '<p>Doing Business records the time and cost associated with the logistical process of exporting and importing goods. Doing Business measures the time and cost (excluding tariffs) associated with three sets of procedures&mdash;documentary compliance, border compliance and domestic transport&mdash;within the overall process of exporting or importing a shipment of goods.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSee above on the further info on score and ranking.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nOnly two largest cities included. Time and cost for domestic transport are&nbsp; not included for these two indicators</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"http://www.doingbusiness.org/data/exploretopics/trading-across-borders\">World Bank</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('689', '48', '8604', 'Proportion of companies that report facing non-tariff measures related obstacles to trade', 'Percentage', '<p>Information on 25 countries available only. There is also more detailed information by sectors/firm size which could be useful to monitor depending on the intervention &ndash; see ITC website for more details.<br />\r\nPlease check the regularity of reporting for you country before using this indicator.</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"http://ntmsurvey.intracen.org/ntm-survey-data/\">International Trade Centre, non-tariff measures surveys<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('690', '48', '8604', 'Number and proportion of rejections at EU borders', 'Number and proportion', '<p>Proportion &ndash; could be proportions rejected based on volume or value or both, depending on the programme. Please specific for your programme.</p>\r\n', '<p><a href=\"https://data.worldbank.org/topic/economy-and-growth?view=chart\">Intervention M&amp;E intervention &ndash; need at least two surveys.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nNumber of rejections can be found on the EC Rapid Alert System for Food and Feed (RASFF) portal</a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary and secondary data', '0'), ('691', '48', '8605', 'Percentage of target adult population (>15 years) with access to financial services disaggregated by service type, sex, age, rural and other relevant groups', 'Percentage', '<p>This may be used as an impact level indicator for some programmes especially if using national level measurements<br />\r\nFor example, financial services could be an account/loan/insurance at bank or financial institution or mobile money service provider</p>\r\n', '<p>National survey, if relevant use sub- national breakdown where available. Need to check if sub-national level surveys are representative of target population.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nProject level surveys (at least twice- pre/post intervention) as part of the project M&amp; E system. Note that this will likely require interviewing individuals who are not direct or indirect beneficiaries of the programme.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data or Primary data', '0'), ('692', '48', '8605', 'World Bank Doing Business \"getting  credit’’ *ranking/score', 'Number/percentage', '<p>Doing Business takes account both collateral rules and credit information. Only firms in the largest city of the economy is considered, please see here [ link to http://www.doingbusiness.org/Methodology/Getting-Credit]&nbsp; for further information.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n*please delete as appropriate. For more information no the ranking and score, please see here [ link to http://www.doingbusiness.org/data/distance-to-frontier]<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>World Bank [link to http://www.doingbusiness.org/data]</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('693', '48', '8605', 'Percent of firms identifying access to finance as a major constraint ', 'Percentage', '<p>If planning to use the World Bank Enterprise Survey information, please check the availability and frequency of the surveys to assess suitable for monitoring purpose. If planning your own enterprise survey as part of the intervention, given the complexity and costs of such surveys, please consider whether this option is viable (e.g. costs/capacity, etc)&nbsp; before using this indicator.</p>\r\n', '<p>Enterprise surveys either carried out by the intervention or from alternative sources, e.g. the World Bank Enterprise surveys or national statistics office. At least two estimates are needed one for the baseline and one at the end of the intervention</p>\r\n', 'Primary or secondary data', '0'), ('694', '48', '8605', 'Number of firms with access to financial services. disaggregated by: - type of service (access to loans, guarantees, banking services etc.) - modalities (electronic or face to face) - user type (sex of head of firm, age of head of firm, etc)', 'Number of firms', '<p>Total amount of financial services obtained (received) by direct or indirect beneficiaries - firms - as a result of an intervention from financial institutions as reported by the beneficiary.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis may also be used at output level depending on whether finance is provided directly or through an intermediary<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAt HQ level, disaggregate by EU financial instruments (e.g. ESFD etc.)</p>\r\n', '<p>This indicator should be included in the intervention M&amp;E system and data should be collected and reported upon by the project (usually the implementing partner) in the course of the project cycle.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('695', '48', '8605', 'Number of individuals with access to financial services, disaggregated by: - type of service (access to loans, guarantees, banking services etc.) - modalities (electronic or face to face) - user type (sex, age, etc)', 'Number of individuals', '<p>At HQ level, disaggregate by EU financial instruments (e.g. EFSD etc.)</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis may also be used at output level depending on whether finance is provided directly or through an intermediary.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('696', '48', '8606', '% of firm sales from new products and/or services supported by programme, disaggregated by product/service type', 'Percentage', '<p>List of eligible products/services to be defined at the beginning of the programme.</p>\r\n', '<p>Enterprise level surveys&nbsp; from the project level M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('697', '48', '8606', 'Number of supported M&SMEs implementing business improvement recommendations provided by supported BDSs, disaggregated by sex of firm owner/head if relevant', 'Number of supported M&SMEs', '', '<p>Enterprise level surveys&nbsp; from the project level M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('698', '48', '8606', 'Number of supported firms investing in additional staff training identified through business services development disaggregated by sex of firm owner/head if relevant', 'Number supported firms', '', '<p>Enterprise level surveys&nbsp; from the project level M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('699', '48', '8606', '(additional) average annual net income reported by supported firms, disaggregated by sex of firm owner/head if relevant', 'Currency (EUR/$/local currency)', '<p>Could replace net income with &quot;gross sales&quot;, &quot;net sales&quot;, &quot;operating profit&quot; depending on the data is available from the firms.</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E involving periodic (annual) surveys if no secondary data (e.g. company annual accounts) is available.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data if available or Primary data', '0'), ('700', '48', '8606', 'Average net income per employee of supported firms, disaggregated by firm size', 'Currency (EUR/$/local currency)', '<p>Could replace net income with &quot;gross sales&quot;, &quot;net sales&quot;, &quot;operating profit&quot; depending on the data is available from the firms.</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E involving periodic (annual) surveys if no secondary data (e.g. company annual accounts) is available.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data if available or Primary data', '0'), ('701', '48', '8606', 'number (or %) of supported firms that report an increase in net income as a results of support, disaggregated by sex of firm owner/head if relevant', 'Number / Percentage', '<p>Could replace net income with &quot;gross sales&quot;, &quot;net sales&quot;, and &quot;operating profit&quot; depending on the data is available from the firms.</p>\r\n', '<p>Periodic surveys of firms supported as part of intervention M&amp;E<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('702', '48', '8606', 'Number of jobs sustained (resulting from the project) in supported firms', 'Number', '<p>Number of full-time equivalent employees at the end of the reporting period. Includes full-time equivalent worked by seasonal, contractual and part time employees. Part-time jobs are converted to full-time equivalent jobs on a prorata basis.</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('703', '48', '8607', 'Average number of days required to file and serve a case ? adjusted from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018) ', 'Number of days', '<p>Time is recorded in calendar days, counted from the moment the plaintiff decides to file the lawsuit in court until payment. This includes both the days when actions take place and the waiting periods between. The average duration of different stages of dispute resolution is recorded: the completion of service of process (time to file and serve the case), the issuance of judgment (time for the trial and obtaining the judgment) and the moment of payment (time for enforcement of the judgment).</p>\r\n', '<p>Court documents and expert analysis of relevant laws and regulations (at least twice as part of intervention M&amp;E)</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data + expert analysis', '0'), ('704', '48', '8607', 'Average number of days required to reach trial and judgement  ? adjusted from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018) ', 'Number of days', '<p>Time is recorded in calendar days, counted from the moment the plaintiff decides to file the lawsuit in court until payment. This includes both the days when actions take place and the waiting periods between. The average duration of different stages of dispute resolution is recorded: the completion of service of process (time to file and serve the case), the issuance of judgment (time for the trial and obtaining the judgment) and the moment of payment (time for enforcement of the judgment).&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Court documents and expert analysis of relevant laws and regulations (at least twice as part of intervention M&amp;E)</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data + expert analysis', '0'), ('705', '48', '8607', 'Average number of days required to enforce judgement ? adjusted from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018) ', 'Number of days', '<p>Time is recorded in calendar days, counted from the moment the plaintiff decides to file the lawsuit in court until payment. This includes both the days when actions take place and the waiting periods between. The average duration of different stages of dispute resolution is recorded: the completion of service of process (time to file and serve the case), the issuance of judgment (time for the trial and obtaining the judgment) and the moment of payment (time for enforcement of the judgment). World Bank Doing Business - see below.</p>\r\n', '<p>Court documents and expert analysis of relevant laws and regulations (at least twice as part of intervention M&amp;E)</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data + expert analysis', '0'), ('706', '48', '8607', 'Average cost of attorney fees as a percentage of the total claim amount  ? taken from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018)', 'Percentage', '<p>Average attorney fees are the fees that Seller (plaintiff) must advance to a local attorney to represent Seller in the standardized case.</p>\r\n', '<p>Expert analysis (at least twice as part of intervention M&amp;E)</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data + expert analysis', '0'), ('707', '48', '8607', 'Average court costs as a percentage of the total claim amount    ? taken from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018)', 'Percentage', '<p>Court costs include all court costs that Seller (plaintiff) must advance to the court, regardless of the final cost to Seller.</p>\r\n', '<p>Expert analysis (at least twice as part of intervention M&amp;E)</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data + expert analysis', '0'), ('708', '48', '8607', 'Enforcement costs as a percentage of the total claim amount   ? taken from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018)', 'Percentage', '<p>Enforcement costs are all costs that Seller (plaintiff) must advance to enforce the judgment through a public sale of Buyer&rsquo;s movable assets, regardless of the final cost to Seller.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Expert analysis (at least twice as part of intervention M&amp;E)</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data + expert analysis', '0'), ('709', '48', '8608', 'Percentage of firms identifying[* transportation electricity/ water access/ internet connectivity etc] as a major constraint ? adjusted from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018)', 'Percentage', '<p>*please adapt/delete as appropriate to the specific infrastructure the intervention is supporting. If more than one sector is supported, please use two separate indicators</p>\r\n', '<p>Enterprise surveys either carried out by the intervention or from alternative sources, e.g. the World Bank Enterprise surveys or national statistics office. At least two estimates are needed one for the baseline and one at the end of the intervention</p>\r\n', 'Primary or secondary data', '0'), ('710', '48', '8608', '% of gross annual sales lost due to  [*insufficient water supply/ power outages/etc] ?  adapted from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018)', 'Percentage', '<p>*please adapt/delete as appropriate to the specific infrastructure the intervention is supporting. If more than one sector is supported, please use two separate indicators</p>\r\n', '<p>Enterprise surveys either carried out by the intervention or from alternative sources, e.g. the World Bank Enterprise surveys or national statistics office. At least two estimates are needed one for the baseline and one at the end of the intervention</p>\r\n', 'Primary or secondary data', '0'), ('711', '48', '8608', 'World Bank Doing Business \"getting  electricity’’ *ranking/score', 'Number/percentage', '<p>Doing Business records all procedures required for a business to obtain a permanent electricity connection and supply for a standardized warehouse. Aspects are efficiency, reliability and transparency are also included, but normally only information from the largest city is collected, please see here [ link to http://www.doingbusiness.org/Methodology/Getting-Electricity]&nbsp; for further information.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n*please delete as appropriate. For more information no the ranking and score, please see XX<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>World Bank [link to http://www.doingbusiness.org/data]</p>\r\n', 'Secondary data', '0'), ('712', '48', '8608', 'Logistics performance infrastructure *index/ranking', 'Number', '<p>The quality of 