ast twice over programme lifetime) as part of intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('743', '48', '8614', 'Number of firms or individuals supported that meet standards and technical requirements (disaggregated by sex, age and firm size)', 'Number of firms or individuals', '<p>Specify elements of the Quality Infrastructure (QI) system targeted for improvement and outline how this would enhance market access.<br />\r\nPlease choose firms or individuals depending on the nature of your project/programme.</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('744', '48', '8614', 'Number of new or renewed conformity schemes-related [certifications/ accreditations/ approvals/ recognitions*] obtained by supported [labs/ firms/ institutions**] for their [products, services or systems**]', 'Number', '<p>Conformity schemes include: International standards (ISO) , Fair Trade, Global GAP, Organic, EU List of approved third country processing establishments for animal products,&nbsp; Multilateral Recognition Agreements (MLA), Mutual Recognition Arrangements (MRA), Agreements on Conformity Assessment and Acceptance, any other relevant schemes.<br />\r\n* delete as appropriate.<br />\r\n** delete depending on the type of economic operator the intervention is supporting.&nbsp;<br />\r\ne.g. number of renewed accreditation obtained by supported labs to issue certification on XXX</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('745', '48', '8614', 'Number of (or Status of**) supported policies regulations or legislations on compliance and standards [developed/ improved/ approved /adopted/ implemented/amended*]', 'Number of policies/reforms', '<p>Could be more specific on the actual reform to tailor to the programme<br />\r\n*delete as appropriate.<br />\r\nThe results level will depend on for the exact nature of the programme and the local context.&nbsp; An indicator on the number of reformed supported is not a good indicator as this is an activity only.<br />\r\n**If only supporting one reform/policy then please use phrase &quot;status of reform X&quot;. .</p>\r\n', '<p>official government publications and expert analysis as part of the intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary or secondary data and expert analysis', '0'), ('746', '48', '8615', 'Number of financial system legal or regulatory reform [developed/ improved/ approved /adopted/ implemented*] implemented (disaggregate by domain of reform and beneficiary)', 'Number of policies', '<p>Reforms can occur at local/micro, subnational, national or regional levels.<br />\r\n*delete as appropriate. The results level will depend on for the exact nature of the intervention and the local context.&nbsp; An indicator on the number of reformed supported is not a good indicator as this is an activity only.<br />\r\nPlease specify the particular reform area of interest to the intervention.</p>\r\n', '<p>Official government publications + expert analysis of implementation.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary or secondary data and expert analysis', '0'), ('747', '48', '8615', 'Number of [*credit registries/credit bureaus] established and functioning with intervention support', 'Number', '<p>*adapt/delete as appropriate<br />\r\n<br />\r\nEstablishment of a credit registry/credit bureaus preferably with online registration and search facility</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('748', '48', '8615', 'Status of payment system', 'Qualitative', '<p>A binary (existing/non-existing) is not a very good target. Please qualify what the mechanism should be like, e.g. fully staff, functioning, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('749', '48', '8616', 'Number of (additional) financial services delivered to individuals and enterprises disaggregated by type and sector', 'Number of financial services', '<p>Additional services are those that are not currently available at local market. They don&#39;t necessarily have to be new product, just new to the current market<br />\r\nPlease also consider the sustainability of &nbsp;financial institution&#39;s ability to provide these services after the project end before using this indicator</p>\r\n', '<p>ex ante and ex post surveys&nbsp; as part of the intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('750', '48', '8616', 'Number of new loans provided to [*individuals/firms] resulting from programme support disaggregated by age, sex, rural/urban and other relevant groups', 'Numbers', '<p>Could be matched to the EFSD results framework indicator on &quot;number of units served among relevant target group&quot;</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('751', '48', '8616', 'Value of new loans provided to [*individuals/firms] resulting from programme support disaggregated by age, sex, rural/urban and other relevant groups', 'Currency', '<p>Could be matched to the EFSD results framework indicator on &quot;Amount of outstanding loans and other sources of financing to relevant target group&quot;</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('752', '48', '8616', 'Average value of new loans provided to firms supported by the programme', 'Currency', '', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('753', '48', '8616', 'Average length of new loans provided to firms supported by the programme', 'Number of months', '', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('754', '48', '8616', 'Number of (additional) financial instruments used by the financial institutions disaggregated by type if relevant', 'Number of financial instruments', '<p>Additional instruments are those that are additional to the institutions, not necessarily completely new innovative instruments that do not exist elsewhere.<br />\r\nPlease also consider the sustainability of the usage after the project ends before using this indicator<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Ex ante and ex post survey as part of the intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('755', '48', '8616', 'volume of new loans made available to financial intermediaries (e.g. banks, microfinance institutions, funds)  ', 'currency ', '<p>Volume of credit lines/guarantees / capital investment extended to financial intermediaries for on lending to target groups (target groups being understood as Microfinance/MSME/Agribusiness/Energy Efficiency/Renewable Energy/Student Loans/Housing Finance/Retail Finance/Total Portfolio/Other to be specified in each instance)<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis can be matched to the EFSD results framework</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('756', '48', '8617', 'Number of people befitting from financial literacy training who can demonstrate/report increased knowledge in financial literacy, disaggregated by sex, age and other relevant groups.', 'Number of people', '<p>Test or evaluation surveys are need to demonstrate increased knowledge in financial literacy&nbsp;&nbsp;before and after the training.</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('757', '48', '8617', '% of supported projects that has received lenders\' financial backing', 'Percentage', '<p>Please specify at the beginning of the project whether there are certain thresholds for financial supported for a project to be counted, e.g. financial value, length of loan, default criteria, etc.</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('758', '48', '8618', 'Status of [regional/ national*] employment/VET strategy', 'Qualitative', '<p>*please adapt/delete as appropriate, and be as specific&nbsp; as possible on the policy/framework<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease do not use binary yes/no, existing/non-existing - be specific on the expected goal/milestone, e.g. fully financed plans revised in consultation with all relevant stakeholders including the private sector, with timelines and roles and responsibilities , and progress to be monitored by lead institution, etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Publications and expert analysis as part of the intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary or secondary data and expert analysis', '0'), ('759', '48', '8618', 'Number of people who have benefitted from institution or workplace based VET/skills development programmes with intervention support', 'Number of people', '<p>could be matched to EU RF&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('760', '48', '8619', 'Number of policies/reforms on labour laws [developed/ improved/ approved /adopted/ implemented*] supported by the programme', 'Number of policies/reforms', '<p>*delete as appropriate.<br />\r\nThe results level will depend on for the exact nature of the programme and the local context.&nbsp; An indicator on the number of reformed supported is not a good indicator as this is an activity only.</p>\r\n', '<p>official government publications and expert analysis as part of the intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary or secondary data and expert analysis', '0'), ('761', '48', '8619', 'Status of legislation/ policy/ reforms on workers\' right on [X]', 'Qualitative', '<p>[X] &ndash; fill in as appropriate. Examples include minimal wage, protection from harassment (inc. sexual harassment), maternity/ parental/ other leave protection, etc.</p>\r\n', '<p>Publications and expert analysis as part of the intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary or secondary data and expert analysis', '0'), ('762', '48', '8619', 'Number of firms supported to comply with labour laws and regulations, disaggregated by sex of firm owner/head if relevant', 'Number of firms', '<p>Please adapt to the context of the intervention, e.g. to specific/named regulations/laws where appropriate.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Enterprise survey - at least before and after intervention as part of intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('763', '48', '8619', 'Number of supported firms reporting additional use of employment contracts, disaggregated by sex of firm owner/head if relevant', 'Number of firms', '', '<p>Enterprise survey - at least before and after intervention as part of intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('764', '48', '8620', 'Status of [*policy/ framework/ regulation reform] on the land administration and tenure system  ? adjusted from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018) ', 'Qualitative', '<p>*please adapt/delete as appropriate, and be as specific&nbsp; as possible on the policy/framework, etc the intervention is supporting, e.g. named regulation on construction permit<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease do not use binary yes/no, existing/non-existing - be specific on the expected goal/milestone, e.g. plans developed in consultation with all relevant stakeholders, with timelines and roles and responsibilities , and progress to be monitored by lead institution, etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('765', '48', '8620', 'Status of land administration agency (one-stop shop) ? adjusted from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018) ', 'Qualitative', '<p>Please do not use binary yes/no, existing/non-existing - be specific on the expected goal/milestone, see example above</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('766', '48', '8620', 'Number of land records digitised and publically available* with the intervention support ? adjusted from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018) ', 'Number', '<p>*could be adapted depending on the intervention context&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('767', '48', '8620', 'Number of women and men who have secure tenure of land disaggregate by sex, age, location of land - EURF', 'Number', '<p>Secure land tenure covers: formal titling, certificates or registration, customary tenure secured by an appropriate legal framework that ensures that customary rights cannot be negated and people cannot be arbitrarily dispossessed of their land. They can be secured by a variety of approaches, from legal to local actions.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis can be matched to an EU RF indicator</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('768', '48', '8623', 'Status of dispute resolution mechanism', 'Qualitative', '<p>Please be as specific as possible and adapt the indicator wording to suit the intervention context.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nA binary (existing/non-existing) is not a very good target. Please qualify what the mechanism should be like, e.g. fully staff, functioning, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('769', '48', '8623', 'Status of  case management system for commercial courts - adjusted from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018) ', 'Qualitative', '<p>Please be as specific as possible and adapt the indicator wording to suit the intervention context.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nA binary (existing/non-existing) is not a very good target. Please qualify what the mechanism should be like, e.g. fully staff, functioning, etc.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('770', '48', '8623', 'Number of cases heard in intervention supported alternative dispute resolutions facilities *', 'Number', '<p>This is a more meaningful indicator than the indicator on number alternative dispute resolution facilities established and operational with intervention support. So please use this indicator where ever possible.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n*Depending on the length of the intervention, you may want to define a period for indicator, e.g. number of cases heard in the first year of operation, or the average per year, etc</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('771', '48', '8623', 'Number alternative dispute resolution facilities established and operational with intervention support - taken from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018) ', 'Number', '<p>Please be as specific as possible and adapt the indicator wording to suit the intervention context.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('772', '48', '8623', 'Number of cases heard in intervention supported commercial court *', 'Number', '<p>This is a more meaningful indicator than the indicator on number of commercial courts&nbsp; established and operational with intervention support. So please use this indicator where ever possible.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n*Depending on the length of the intervention, you may want to define a period for indicator, e.g. number of cases heard in the first year of operation, or the average per year, etc</p>\r\n', '', '', '0'), ('773', '48', '8623', 'Number of commercial courts established and operational with intervention support - taken from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018) ', 'Number', '', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('774', '48', '8623', 'Number of electronic complaints filled using the electronic facility established with the intervention support *- adjusted from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018)', 'Number', '<p>*Depending on the length of the intervention, you may want to define a period for indicator, e.g. number of cases heard in the first year of operation, or the average per year, etc</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('775', '48', '8624', 'Status of [*regional/national *regulatory/policy/framework on *affordable connectivity]', 'Qualitative', '<p>*Please adapt/deleted to fit the specific policy the intervention is supporting. Please do be as specific as possible<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease do not use binary yes/no, existing/non-existing - be as specific on the expected goal/milestone, e.g. electrification plan developed in consultation with all relevant stakeholders, with timelines and roles and responsibilities , and progress to be monitored by lead institution, etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system and potentially expert analysis of government documents</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('776', '48', '8624', 'Status of independent regulator of [*water/transport/ICT/etc]', 'Qualitative', '<p>*Please adapt/deleted to fit the specific policy the intervention is supporting. Please do be as specific as possible<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease do not use binary yes/no, existing/non-existing - be specific on the expected goal/milestone, e.g. independent regulator set up, fully financed/staffed with a clear mandate, etc.</p>\r\n', '', '', '0'), ('777', '48', '8625', 'Status of framework for [*grid electrification/mini-grids/stand-alone system]  - adjusted from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018) ', 'Qualitative', '<p>*please adapt/delete as appropriate. Please adapt the&nbsp; specific policy the intervention is supporting where needed, e.g. named regulation on minigrid tariffs, or named policy for subsidies for energy storage system, etc<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease do not use binary yes/no, existing/non-existing - be specific on the expected goal/milestone - see example above</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system and potentially expert analysis of government documents</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0');
INSERT INTO `legacy_web_indicators` VALUES ('778', '48', '8625', 'Status of [*policy/legal framework/expansion plan]  for renewable energy - adjusted from the ICR Diagnostic Toolkit (2018) ', 'Qualitative', '<p>*please adapt/delete as appropriate. Please be as specific&nbsp; as possible on the policy/framework, etc the intervention is supporting<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease do not use binary yes/no, existing/non-existing - be specific on the expected goal/milestone - see example above</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system and potentially expert analysis of government documents</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('779', '48', '8625', 'Status of [*national plan/policy/framework] on energy efficiency', 'Qualitative', '<p>*please adapt/delete as appropriate. Please be as specific&nbsp; as possible e.g. named regulation/policy at national level, specific policy on carbon pricing, EE incentives, etc.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease do not use binary yes/no, existing/non-existing - be specific on the expected goal/milestone - see example above</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system and potentially expert analysis of government documents</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('780', '48', '8626', 'Number of firms or individuals that utilise business development services supported by intervention, disaggregated by type of service, type of entity, firm size, and sex', 'Number of firms or individuals', '<p>BDS are services that improve the performance of the enterprise, its access to markets, and its ability to compete. BDS are designed to serve individual businesses, as opposed to the larger business community.</p>\r\n', '<p>The data should be collected from the BDS service providers as part of intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('781', '48', '8626', 'Number of firms or individuals that are aware and acquire business development services, disaggregated by sex or sex of firm owners/head', 'Number of firms or individuals', '<p>Please choose firms or individuals depending on the nature of your intervention</p>\r\n', '<p>Survey ex ante and ex post<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('782', '48', '8626', 'Number of additional business development services providers offering relevant advice/training on [X] with intervention support', 'Number of BDS providers', '<p>[X] &ndash; to be specified that is relevant for the intervention</p>\r\n', '<p>Periodic (at least ex ante, ex post) surveys as part of the intervention M&amp;E system<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('783', '48', '8626', 'Number of businesses introducing a new product/service to the market with intervention support', 'Number', '<p>This could be adapted to be more specific to the intervention context. You should specify whether the product/service that is new to the firm or new to the main market</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('784', '48', '8626', 'Number of businesses applying Sustainable Consumption and Production practices with intervention support, disaggregated by size of firm, sex of owner', 'Number', '<p>This could be adapted to be more specific to the intervention context.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWorking definition of SCP &quot;the production and use of services and related products, which respond to basic needs and bring a better quality of life while minimising the use of natural resources and toxic materials as well as the emissions of waste and pollutants over the life cycle of the service or product so as not to jeopardise the needs of future generations&rdquo;&nbsp; (Oslo Symposium, 1994). This includes, for example, the production of clean energy, the manufacturing of recycled goods, products that are certified in accordance with sustainability standards etc.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('785', '48', '8626', 'Number of businesses applying digital solutions with intervention support, disaggregated by size of firm, sex of owner', 'Number', '<p>This could be adapted to be more specific to the intervention context.</p>\r\n', '<p>Intervention M&amp;E&nbsp;system</p>\r\n', 'Primary data', '0'), ('791', '45', '8460', 'Status of laws/regulations determining standards of evidence collection processes are in line with international standards', 'Status of', '<p>If the Action will support the development of laws/regulations ensuring that evidence-collection processes are aligned with international norms, this is an appropriate output-level indicator.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p>Legislation/policies developed/updated with the support of the Action</p>\r\n', 'Primary', '0'), ('792', '45', '8450', 'Average number of detainees per cell', 'Number of', '', '<p>Administrative data</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0'), ('793', '45', '8450', 'Number of detainees per penitentiary officer', 'Number of', '', '<p>Administrative data</p>\r\n', 'Secondary', '0');
COMMIT;

